<HEADLINE> Takahama Wins Third Amateur world Straight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Middleweight Tatsuro Takahama of
Japan become the first wrestler to win three straight titles at
the amateur Sumo World Championships on Saturday after shoving
Germany's Eduard Grams out of the ring.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian Svetoslav Binev won the lightweight title match by
throwing down Atsuhiro Ibata of Japan. Binev is the first
Bulgarian ever to win a sumo championship.
</P>
<P>
Wrestlers from 32 countries gathered at Tokyo's Ryogoku
Kokugikan Sumo Arena for the seventh annual tournament.
</P>
<P>
The heavyweight and openweight title matches and the team
competition will be held on Sunday, the tournament's second and
final day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
