<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, December 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Palestinians continued anti-Israel demonstrations
across the West Bank on Saturday, days before U.S. President Bill
Clinton sets foot on the soil under Palestinian self-rule.
</P>
<P>
Near the Ariel El Jewish settlement north of Ramallah, hundreds
of Palestinians tried to break into the settlement but were fought
back by Israeli soldiers. (Israel-Palestinian Demonstrations)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- The Afghan Taliban Militia have accused Iran of
providing anti-personnel mines to the rival opposition of the
Northern Alliance, Bakhtar News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Senior Taliban official responsible for information and culture
Amir Khan Muttaqi said that 400 Iran-made anti-personnel mines
were recently unearthed and seized in Bangi district of Takhar
province. (Afghan-Taliban-Iran)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak said the goal of his
mediation between Turkey and Syria in October was to help them
solve their disputes in a peaceful way. (Egypt-Turkey-Syria)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Former Chilean leader Augusto Pinochet's lawyers are
seeking to overturn the ruling against the general because of
bias, The Guardian newspaper reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
They are seeking the annulment on the grounds that the wife of
one of the five Law Lords, who ruled out on November 25th that
Pinochet was not immune from prosecution, works for Amnesty
International. (UK-Pinochet-Lawyer) 
</P>
