<HEADLINE> S. Africa Signs 13 Agreements With India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 5 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and India
signed 13 agreements Saturday at the end of a two-day meeting of
the Indo-South African Joint Commission in Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
The treaties included cooperation in the fields of air
transport, trade, science and technology, tourism, geology and
mineral resources and culture.
</P>
<P>
Nine other agreements are to be finalized.
</P>
<P>
South African Deputy Foreign Minister Aziz Pahad, who chaired
the meeting, said: "Relations with India are fundamental to South
Africa's foreign policy."
</P>
<P>
He said trade had grown to 5 billion Rand (880 million U.S.
Dollars) between the two countries over the last five years.
</P>
</TEXT>
