<HEADLINE> Notorious Gangsters Arrested in Addis: Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 5 (Xinhua) --Police said Saturday that
they have apprehended 310 notorious gangsters in the capital
Addis Ababa over the last three months.
</P>
<P>
Belete Gulantaw, Addis Ababa Administration Police
Commissioner, said here that the alleged criminals were caught
when they were operating individually and in group.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted Belete as saying that the
criminals include robbers, gun-runners, burglars, auto-thieves
and drug-traffickers.
</P>
<P>
Belete commended the role of the public in helping
the police successfully track down the criminals.
</P>
<P>
Gold accessories, T.V. sets, video cassette recorders,
electronic materials, auto parts and various utensils were found
in the hands of the thieves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
