<HEADLINE> Mubarak Delivers Assad's Message to Demirel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Egyptian President
Hosni Mubarak delivered a message from Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad to his Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel on
Turkey-Syria ties.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak, who arrived here Saturday noon for a two-day official
visit to Turkey, said at a joint press conference with Demirel
that "Assad is happy with the defusing of the crisis between
Syria and Turkey" over the Kurdish rebel issue.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak said, "Assad explained to me about his views on the
Turkish-Syrian ties and on his wish that Syria and Turkey will
develop a productive cooperation in the direction of joint
interests."
</P>
<P>
However, Mubarak did not bring any concrete proposal on
improving the Turkish-Syrian ties to the Turkish president.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Demirel expressed his gratitude to Mubarak for his
mediation in defusing the crisis between Ankara and Damascus over
the Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK), outlawed in Turkey. .
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian president shuttled between Ankara and Damascus in
early October to ease tension heightened after Turkey threatened
to launch military strikes against Syria if Damascus continues to
support the PKK.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Syria signed a security cooperation deal following
Egyptian mediation, which resulted in Syria's expulsion of the
PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan was detained by the Italian police upon his arrival
in Rome by a Russian Airlines passenger plane on November 12.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 14-year-old separatist war for
self rule in southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over 37,000
lives in conflicts since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
