<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian Games Opens in Bangkok (update) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The 13th Asian Games opened in
the Thai capital here on Sunday with an extravaganza ceremony as
Thailand is surfacing from its most severe financial crisis in
decades.
</P>
<P>
As prelude performance started at 18:00, Thailand's King
Bhumibol Adulyadej opened the Games at 20:24 in the 60,000-seat
Rajmangala Stadium of the Hua Mark Sports Complex here.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing, who is on a four-day official
visit to Thailand, attended the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Also attending the ceremony were leaders of the international
sports organizations including the International Olympic Committee
President Juan Antonio Samaranch and the Olympic Council of Asia
President Sheikh Ahmad al-Fahad al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
About 10,000 athletes and officials from 41 countries and
regions are participating in the Games, which features 377 gold
medals in 36 disciplines including Asian specialities such as
kabaddi and sepak takraw.
</P>
<P>
The march-in started from Cambodia according to the order of
the Thai language, and Saudi Arabia, which withdrew from the Games
at the last minutes, was represented by a flag bearer.
</P>
<P>
Each participating team was escorted by a Miss Thailander
holding its plate, while Sri Lankan put up a peculiar show with
six dancers in bright costumes.
</P>
<P>
However, several Thai beauty queens could not stand the hot
weather and were taken out on stretchers after they fainted in the
stadium.
</P>
<P>
King Bhumibol Adulyadej, a jazz composer, made the proclamation
to open the Games and released a Royal pigeon before songs written
by himself were played by the Bangkok Symphony Orchestra.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's only Olympic gold medalist Somrak Khamsing, as the
last runner of the torch relay, became the cynosure of the whole
stadium by setting the cauldron alight, sending the whole audience
into elated acclamation.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is hosting the last Asian Games of the century, the
fourth time being held in Bangkok after prvious successes in 1966,
1970 and 1978.
</P>
<P>
Despite the withdrawal of 17 sports teams which forced the
organizers to make three re-draws in some events, Sunday night's
performance, a feast-for-eye mixture of songs and dances by local
pop singers and performers in colorful costumes, reflected the
country's determination to further attain Asian unity and to
overcome the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
In the first act "The Dawn", dusk was transformed to dawn when
the Sun God made its spectacular entrance at the stadium,
symbolizing the wit of Asian people to overcome any obstacles
ahead.
</P>
<P>
The three-hour ceremony featured 7,614 performers in
enlightening performances with the theme of "Friendship Beyond
Frontiers".
</P>
<P>
A martial art show depicted Asian unity, which was enhanced by
a later episode with four swan floats, each tied with a giant
balloon, to symbolize the sun, moon, earth and a giant lotus.
</P>
<P>
After the display of fireworks and laser lights, the Royal
anthem was played to conclude the ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
