<HEADLINE> Japanese Dominates Final-leg of FIM Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Youichi Nakajima won the
final-leg of the FIM Asia Road Racing Championship Sunday at the
Johor Circuit in Malaysia's Pasir Gudang, preventing a clean
sweep by the Thais, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese Nakajima took the 250cc title by riding a Yamaha
TZR 250 in 24:55.97 to collect full points and the overall title
with 95 points.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's Kuan Meng Heng was timed at 25:02.86 for second and
also took second in the overall standings with 76 points.
</P>
<P>
The 150cc category was a Thai-dominated race with ace rider
Direk Achawong leading the way with a time of 20:36.62. He was
closely followed by teammate Christmas Wilairoj with a time of
20:36.73.
</P>
<P>
In the 125cc class, Thailand's Eakrach Panbubpha took the
checkered flag with a race time of 17:47.83. His 75 points total
also gave him the overall title.
</P>
<P>
Second place went to Malaysia's Shahrun Nizam, who clocked
17:48.10. Another Malaysian, Mohd Hisham Ngadin, was third in
18:00.33.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's Mohd Faisal Yahya finished second overall in the
125cc category after his fourth placing today earned him 55
points.
</P>
<P>
Thai rider Ampron Siriphat was the champion of the Underbone
110cc category with 56 points. Another Thai rider Suhathai
Chamsub, 10th place-finisher, clinched overall second place with
50 points. 
