outsprinted Japan's Nobuyuki Sato in the final two kilometers to
claim the Fukuoka International Marathon race on Sunday,
according to reports.
</P>
<P>
Kabiga completed the 42.195 kilometers with a time of 2 hours,
8 minutes 42 seconds, six second faster than Sato, who was second
in 2:08.48 finish, followed by three other Japanese _ Tadayuki
Ojima in 2:09.10, Noriaki Igarashi in 2:09.38 and Muneyuki Ojima
in 2:09.50.
</P>
