ahead of the leaders group of 20 runners 11 kilometers into the
race.
</P>
<P>
But Sato and Ojima caught up with him after 38 kilometers and
the three ran shoulder-to-shoulder for a while.
</P>
<P>
Sato briefly took the lead, but Kabiga spurted after 40
kilometers and went on to win.
</P>
<P>
A field of 117, including 14 non-Japanese, competed in the
52th marathon race.  
</P>
