<HEADLINE> Science And Technology Development In Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region has developed its science and technology since
it was established in 1958.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, its science and technology development ranked fourth
in the country, and its ratio of sales of scientific and
technological products to total income was the second highest in
China. The region is a leader in high-tech development.
</P>
<P>
This is in stark contrast with the early years of the New China
after 1949 when people here had almost no idea about science.
</P>
<P>
The region had more than 220 science and technology institutes
by the end of 1997, employing more than 740,000 people.
</P>
<P>
It has launched 8 science and technology projects since 1996 in
agriculture, helping the poor with science and technology, and in
aquaculture. Guangxi's per hectare grain output has increased 15
percent.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi has a 1,595-kilometer coastline and has started over
120 marine science and technology projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
