<HEADLINE> Marine Aquatic Products Industry Growing Fast In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The marine aquatic products
industry has been contributing an increasing amount to the
economic growth of the coastal city of Qingdao in east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The sector now accounts for 38.8 percent of the output value of
the local agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
In the January-November period of this year, the city produced
730,000 tons of aquatic products, valued at 3.8 billion yuan (458
million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The volume of aquatic products from the sea in the 11-month
period rose 18 percent on a yearly basis, and the volume from
freshwater cultivation rose nearly 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
The city of Qingdao has preferential policies to advance local
aquaculture industry, especially in tidal areas.
</P>
<P>
The city now has more than 300 aquatic-products processing
companies and centers for cultivating saltwater fish, shellfish
and freshwater crabs.  
</P>
