<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Central Bank Announces New Interest Rate Cuts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China
(POBC), China's central bank, announced a new package of interest
rate cuts today that will take effect Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the bank, they are an important way to boost the
economy by lowering interest rates on bank deposits and loans by
an average of 0.5 percentage points, and interest rates on
deposits and loans of the central bank reserve funds.
</P>
<P>
Interest rates on demand and three-month deposits will remain
unchanged, interest rates for other deposits and all loans will be
cut. The bank will also cut interest rates on reserve funds and on
central bank loans to financial institutions from 3.51 percent to
3.24 percent and from 5.61 percent to 5.06 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
It says that the rate cuts are tied to the latest round of
reductions on interest rates by developed countries, giving China
room to lower its rates.
</P>
<P>
Consumer goods have continued to decline in price, although at
a lower pace and as a result real interest rates remain high. The
performance of state-owned enterprises is improving slightly, the
bank says, but they are not regarded as having completely
recovered.
</P>
<P>
The bank has taken into consideration of the interests of
enterprises, individuals, and commercial banks as well as the
balance between interest rates of the renminbi and foreign
currencies.
</P>
<P>
The bank says that all Chinese financial institutions must
abide by its regulations and that illegal raising of rates will be
penalized in accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
The central bank has reduced interest rates three times since
last October and this has had a positive effect in counteracting
the current financial turmoil in some Asian nations and the
effects of the devastating floods this summer, it says.
</P>
<P>
The bank predicts that the cuts will be important in increasing
the money supply by some time next year, lowering operating costs
of industrial and commercial firms, and increasing the amount of
consumer loans, domestic consumer demand, and of exports to have
rapid and healthy economic development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
