<HEADLINE> Chinese Nation-wide Legal Service Hotline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- China is planning a nation-wide
legal hotline by the end of the year or the beginning of next year
to help people get advice from justice departments.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Justice Gao Changli told a teleconference today
that this is something new but with a great deal of social use for
today's world. The number 1600148 is at a special service center in
the Ministry.
</P>
<P>
By now, 118 counties or cities have legal service
hotline. Dongming County in Shandong Province was the first in the
country, when it opened one on March 16.
</P>
<P>
Another 178 counties or cities in 18 provinces and autonomous
regions have chosen to set them up in the coming year, according
to the minister, who explains that they help people deal with
various matters or disputes to look out for their own interests in
accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
He says that the hotline at the grass-roots level will provide
special services for China's 900 million farmers who can learn
more from the hotline about the law.  
</P>
</TEXT>
