<HEADLINE> one Killed in Plane Crash in Istanbul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A small passenger plane of
Sonmez Air crashed at Istanbul Ataturk Airport in Turkey,
killing one pilot.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency said the crash of the
plane occurred at 12:10 local time (10:10 GMT) when it was about
to land on the airport.
</P>
<P>
The plane hit an empty container near the apron of the airport
and caused fire, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
However, there was no passenger on board and one of the two
pilots was killed in the crash.
</P>
<P>
An investigation into the cause of the crash is
underway. 
</P>
