<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Divers Face No Serious Challenge in Platform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese women divers will face
no serious challenge in the platform event at the 13th Asian
Games, said Chinese ace diver Li Na.
</P>
<P>
China will field two divers of Li Na and Cai Yuyan in the
women's platform to stage a two-way assault on the gold.
</P>
<P>
"If we make no big mistake, the gold should be ours," said the
14-year-old Li Na.
</P>
<P>
The diminutive diver said her 16-year-old teammate Cai will be
her tough opponent in the competition and no other diver in sight
could bring any trouble to her.
</P>
<P>
But she acknowledged that Irina Vyguzova of Kazakhstan will be
a diver to beat in the women's three-meter springboard.
</P>
<P>
"Irina is an excellent diver," said Li, "If she gives her best
in the competition, she has the chance to snatch the gold away
from Chinese divers."
</P>
<P>
Chinese diver Guo Jingjing and Yang Lan will enter the women's
three-meter springboard competition.
The diving competition of the games will start on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
