<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Privatize Container Terminal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The privatization of the
Tanzania Harbor Authority (THA)'s container terminal will be
completed in July next year, according to a senior official at
the Ministry of Communications and Transport.
</P>
<P>
Salim Msoma, the permanent secretary in the ministry, was
quoted by local newspapers on Sunday as saying that inception
report for the privatization purpose was submitted to the
government for comment in July this year and that the
concessionaire is expected to be in place by next May.
</P>
<P>
Presenting a paper at a meeting here Saturday between donor
communities and permanent secretaries from all the Tanzanian
ministries, Msoma said consultants are working on assets
evaluation, employee issues and all operational matters of the
container terminal, Msoma said.
</P>
<P>
He further said the entire process of privatization is being
implemented by the Presidential Sector Reform Commission (PSRC)
and that his ministry is just monitoring the process.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, organized by the Ministry of Finance, brought
together representatives from Italy, Norway, Germany,
Switzerland, Finland, Japan, Denmark, the United States, as well
as the World Bank and European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
