<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO Extraction Force to Be Deployed Over Weekend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A NATO-led extraction force
will be deployed over this weekend in Macedonia as the backup for
the international verifiers for the Kosovo cease-fire.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of the extraction force, which will be
consisted of troops from France, Britain, Germany, Italy, the
Netherlands and Greece, will be in place for extraction operations
after NATO gave the deployment order on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The multinational force, which was formed at the request of the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), would
be on standby to rush to the rescue of the OSCE-led verification
mission in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The extraction force, mainly paratroopers, will be able to
react within 30 to 60 minutes if the weather permits to pull out
the verifiers or to rescue the verifiers taken hostage.
</P>
<P>
NATO approved the extraction force concept in mid-November but
the newly-elected government of Macedonia approved the deployment
of the NATO-led force last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An official at NATO's supreme allied command in Europe told the
press last month that the OSCE verifiers would, in adverse
circumstances, first resort to the Yugoslav authorities for help.
</P>
<P>
In a deal reached between Belgrade and the OSCE, it is the
responsibility of the Yugoslav authorities to guarantee the safety
of the 2,000-member verification mission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981206.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Skaters Take Four Golds at World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese speed skaters won four
gold medals at the short track speed skating World Cup series
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 1000-meter finals, China's Yang Yang (A)
claimed the gold with a time of one minute 40.81 seconds,
followed by her teammate Yang Yang (S) in 1:40.92 and Wang Chunlu
of China in 1:41.00.
</P>
<P>
China's Li Jiajun snatched the gold in the men's 1000m finals,
clocking 1:35.10. Japan's Terao Satoru and Kim Dong-sung of South
Korea registered a second and third time of 1:35.23 and 1:35.29
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Yang Yang (A) defeated Choi Min-Kyung of South Korea for the
champion in the women's 3000m finals. Their time were 5:43.71 and
5:43.94 respectively. Yang Yang (S) finished third in 5:44.21.
</P>
<P>
The gold of the men's 3000m event went to South Korean Lee
Jun-Hwan who was timed at 5:24.20. Van Vossel Simon of Belgium
got the silver and Mathieu Turcotte of Canada bronze.
</P>
<P>
China also won the title in the women's 3000m relay race,
while the title of the men's 5000m relay went to Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
