</P>
<P>
-- The Egyptian banks will start dealing with Euro, the
European single currency, as of next month, said the Central Bank
Governor Ismael Hassan.
</P>
<P>
The Euro exchange rate will be fixed and stable, with interest
rates standing at 3 percent. And dealing with the Euro will remain
on paper through 2002, after which notes will be issued.
</P>
