<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Israeli Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Israeli newspapers on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Post:
</P>
<P>
-- Dozens of Palestinians were wounded on Saturday during
clashes with Israeli soldiers in several West Bank towns and east
Jerusalem as they protested against the detention of Palestinian
prisoners in Israeli jails. Meanwhile, several hundred Palestinian
prisoners in Israeli jails launched hunger strikes in the same day.
</P>
<P>
Haaretz:
</P>
<P>
-- The central committee of the Palestinian National Council
(PNC) is to meet next Thursday to vote to reaffirm the
abolition of the clauses in the Palestinian Charter which call
for the elimination of Israel. The decision to convene the PNC
was made Friday night at a meeting of the executive committee
of the Palestinian Liberation Organization in Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Yediot Aharonot:
</P>
<P>
-- Two Israeli soldiers and one soldier of the pro-Israeli
South Lebanese Army (SLA) were wounded in an exchange of fire
between two sides in South Lebanon. The incident occured after
the SLA militiamen opened fire on Israeli troops whom they
mistook for Hezbollah guerrillas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
