<HEADLINE> Men's 5000m Record Shattered Twice at Speed Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- China and South Korea have
both shattered world record in men's 5000 meters relay race at
the short-track speed skating World Cup Series, the officials
confirmed here today.
</P>
<P>
Hosts China slashed the previous mark of 7:00.042 by over
eight seconds, clocking 6:51.930 in the semi-finals on Saturday
night, while South Korea finished 6:53.61. 
</P>
