<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Reports High Fruit Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Province, an
industrial production base in northeast China, produced 3.7
million tons of fruits this year, with the total output value
exceeding five billion yuan, said local sources.
</P>
<P>
The per capita share of fruits of the province exceeds 90 kg,
about 30 kg more than the world's average, according to
information from the provincial bureau of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The province now grows more than 666,000 hectares of fruit
trees and has listed 30 specialized fruit production counties,
involving 1.6 million rural households.
</P>
<P>
Fruit market network construction and emergence of services for
fruit packaging and transportation have in turn promoted
development of fruit growing, said a local agricultural official.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 15 specialized fruit markets, with their
total volume of transactions exceeding two billion yuan a year.
There are also more than 30 fruit processing enterprises which are
generating about 100 million yuan of pre-tax profits annually.
The output value of fruit packaging industry is estimated at 500
million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
