<HEADLINE> Marathon to Boost Ayutthaya's Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The women's marathon held in
Thailand's Ayutthaya will boost the ancient city's tourism,
governor of Ayutthaya Yuwat Vuthimedhi said here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"After the competition, the name of Ayutthaya will appear in
newspapers, television and other media, so all the world will know
our city," Wuthimedhi said.
</P>
<P>
Ayutthaya, some 70 kilometers north of Bangkok, has a history
of 417 years. It had been the capital of ancient Thailand in the
18th century.
</P>
<P>
"The Thai government and the Organizing Committee of the Asian
Games seleted Ayutthaya as the starting point of the marathon
competition to make it better known to the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
The governor said that they have made full preparation for the
competition and everything has been improved especially its
enviorment and transportation.
</P>
<P>
"We have planted a lot of trees and flowers along the streets,
and encouraged the students to cheer for the athletes," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Ayutthaya will stage more marathons and other
sports competitions in the future.
</P>
<P>
"If so, Ayutthaya will be more famous," he said. "More and more
tourists will come to Ayutthaya." 
</P>
</TEXT>
