<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 48,000 Road Accidents Recorded in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Over 48,000 road accidents have
been recorded in Zimbabwe so far this year in which 2,000 people
were killed and the Zimbabwe Traffic Safety Board (ZTSB) predicts
that more accidents will occur during the forthcoming festive
period.
</P>
<P>
ZTSB spokesman Romaldo Jokonya said here Saturday that the
accidents had surpassed those of last year by about 5,000,
killing about 2,031 people, 700 more than last year, the Sunday
Mail reported.
</P>
<P>
The accidents include a record three-bus disaster, in which a
total of 77 people died and many others were seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Jokonya said the increase in road accidents was caused by
motorists' rising lack of respect on proper road usage by most
motorists.
</P>
<P>
In a desperate bid to curb the carnage on the roads, a bill
was being drafted to clamp down on speeding in the wake of
numerous bus accidents which have claimed thousands of lives
since the country's independence in 1980, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ZTSB was carrying out a campaign which was specifically
aimed at reducing road accidents during the forthcoming festive
season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
