<HEADLINE> South China Province Helping With Three Gorges Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
province, growing fast economically, has provided economic
assistance to the Three Gorges Area to help with its relocation
drive and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, Guangdong has provided 199 million yuan in
financial aid to the area, 66.48 millon yuan of that being free,
local officials say.
</P>
<P>
The funds have been used for 51 construction projects, 17
schools, helping 3,300 school drop-outs return to school, and for
providing training to 2,305 people.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong has spent a lot on the area's infrastructure to help
improve the economic environment. Some 59.7 million yuan has been
for power, telecommunications and transportation construction.
</P>
<P>
Authorities in Guangdong have encouraged local enterprises to
develop cooperative projects with enterprises in the Three Gorges
Area and has helped some enterprises in the area move to new areas
beneficial to technological development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
