<HEADLINE> Quann Improves U.S. 200m Breaststroke Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 5 (Xinhua) -- 14-year-old Megan Quann
established an American record in the women's 200-meter
breaststroke Saturday on the final day of the U.S. Open short
course swimming championships in College Station, Texas.
</P>
<P>
Quann's winning time of two minutes, 25.52 seconds improved
the mark set by Kristine Quance in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia's Martina Moravcova, who set European records in
winning the women's 100m butterfly and 200m individual medley the
past two days, won the women's 100m freestyle in 54.23 seconds.
</P>
<P>
