<HEADLINE> Hunan Province Plans Agricultural Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
plans to double the income of farmers and increase annual farm
output by some six percent by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The province also plans to substantially improve both
infrastructure and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Hunan scientists will introduce high technology to optimize the
agricultural structure, and the non-agricultural output value will
account for 80 percent of the total rural economy within five
years.
</P>
<P>
They will establish a timber tree base covering 30,000 ha. and
will build embankments to protect 15,300 ha around the Dongting
Lake area.
</P>
<P>
Hunan will also encourage development of rural enterprises,
increase inputs to agriculture, redouble poverty relief efforts
and establish agricultural commodity bases in 90 percent of its
counties and townships.
</P>
<P>
The total agricultural output for 1999 is expected to increase
by six percent, according to a local official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
