<HEADLINE> Ecuadoran Exports to Andean Community Drop by 13 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's exports to the
Community of Andean Nations dropped by 13 percent in the first 10
months of this year, the Central Bank of Ecuador said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Exports between January and October stood at 465 million
U.S. dollars, compared with 534 million dollars for the same
period of 1997, according to the bank.
</P>
<P>
Ecuadoran exports to Colombia and Peru during the period
dropped by 21.5 percent and 9.9 percent respectively while its
exports to Venezuela rose by 27 percent and to Bolivia by 10
percent.
</P>
<P>
