<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Crack Down on Quacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A committee has been appointed
by the Health Ministry of Sri Lanka to crack down on quacks and
prosecute them in courts, Health Ministry sources said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent survey conducted by the Health Ministry,
there are more than 10,000 quacks practicing Western medicine all
over the country. Some of them who had practiced Western medicine
after passing as Ayurvedic medical, an indigenous medical,
practitioners.
</P>
<P>
The situation has resulted in difficulties in curbing the
spread of infectious diseases, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The committee will begin apprehending the quacks from January
1, next year, and assistance from voluntary organizations and
non-governmental organizations has been sought in this regard, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
New legislation has been enacted to enhance the punishment, the
sources said, adding that under the new legislation a quack who
was hitherto fined only 7.4 U.S. dollars could be fined up to 740
dollars and sentenced to six months in prison. 
</P>
</TEXT>
