<HEADLINE> Thai Police Arrest Minister's Adviser </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A police official confirmed press reports on Sunday that
Asawayuth Osathanukrob, 31, also the public relations director of
a major consumer goods manufacturer, was arrested on Friday night
for illegal possession of cocaine and firearms.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Office of the Narcotics Control Board in a
raid found 94 grams of cocaine in nine paper packets in his
possession, along with a handgun.
</P>
<P>
The raid was made after a tip-off that Asawayuth had bought the
cocaine from a drug trafficker for 100,000 baht (2,777 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The suspect confessed that the drug was meant to be resold to
his high-society friends and others.
</P>
<P>
Asawayuth was handed over to the Police Narcotics Suppression
Bureau. 
