<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Wild Animal World to Be Built </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The Jindian State Forest Park
in the city of Kunming, capital of China's Yunnan Province, and a
Hong Kong investment company have signed an agreement to build a
wild animal world here to show the province's rich plant and
animal life.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan has more than 17,000 varieties of plants, or 62.9
percent of the national total, and 1,737 species of animals,
accounting for 54.9 percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The Province has 126 species of wild animals that have state
protection, 23 of which are unique to Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project consists of a wild animal
exhibition zone on 149 hectares of land and a 138-hectare forest
ecology tourism zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
