<HEADLINE> Sweden Wins Seventh Davis Cup Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Sweden won
their seventh Davis Cup title on Saturday when they took an
unbeatable 3-0 lead over Italy in the final in Milan, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Jonas Bjorkmann and Nicklas Kulti sealed Sweden's victory by
eliminating Italian pair pairing Diego Nargiso and Davide
Sanguinetti 7-6 (7-1), 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Magnus Norman defeated Italian Andrea Gaudenzi 6-7
(9-11), 7-6 (7-0), 4-6, 6-3 in the first singles match on Friday.
The Italian retired with a torn shoulder tendon with the score at
6-6 in the fifth set.
</P>
<P>
Magnus Gustafsson had beaten Sanguinetti 6-1, 6-4, 6-0 in
Friday's second singles match to give the Swedish team a 2-0
overnight lead. 
