<HEADLINE> Cuba Officially Declares Christmas Holiday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban government has
declared Christmas a legal holiday, the official newspaper Granma
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A Cuban Council of State decree signed by President Fidel
Castro said that starting this year, the 25th day of December
becomes now "a holiday for Christians and non-Christians,
believers or non-believers alike."
</P>
<P>
Christmas has not been an official holiday in Cuba since 1969.
