<HEADLINE> Schmitt Wrests Third Win in World Cup Ski </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Martin Schmitt
benefited from a mistake by double Olympic champion Kazuyoshi
Funaki on Saturday to claim his third consecutive win of the
World Cup ski jumping season in Chamonix, France.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old German cleanly landed jumps of 101.5 and 94
meters to finish with a winning total of 242.5.
</P>
<P>
Finland's Janne Ahonen finished second for the third time in a
row with 240.5 while Funaki, the leader after the opening jump,
came to third with 239.0.
</P>
<P>
Two-time World Cup champion Andreas Goldberger, his cocaine
problems and battles with the Austrian ski federation behind him,
indicated he was ready to challenge for the title finishing
seventh with a score of 220.0 and jumps of 95.5 and 88.0 meters.
</P>
<P>
After three of the season's 30 events, Schmitt leads the World
Cup standings with 300 points followed by Ahonen on 240 and
Funaki with 170. 
</P>
